<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="1" id="1eb8a662-2efb-5f77-ba6f-8dd529c2a286" activityNameId="991d93d2-bf5c-4f26-b1b9-46e02003c780" parentActivityId="286d8436-60cd-4aeb-b964-6cc7f8555a95" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">market for styrene</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce 'styrene',  within the geography of Global.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the supply of 'styrene',  to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">This is the market for  'styrene', in the Global geography.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">styrene', is a plastic product of fossil origin. It is a precursor substance meant to be used for the further production of plastics. It is liquid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure with a sweet, floral odour. The product is used in the following applications and sectors: fillers, putties, plasters, modelling clay and coating products.</text>
        </generalComment>
        <tag>ConvertedDataset</tag>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="3a73c9e2-b73a-41fb-9a63-9279f04c4582">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">EcoSpold01Categories</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">plastics/monomers</classificationValue>
      </classification>
